{NORTH might jump-shift, but with no 5-card suit prefers to use Jacoby 2NT.

SOUTH shows some extra strength plus a 5-card \C suit with his 4\C bid. 

When NORTH's Blackwood discovers two Aces in SOUTH's hand she goes right to 7\S. 
She knows SOUTH has only three red cards and her \HA 
\D A K will take care of them. She figures SOUTH can ruff 
out any \C losers.}

